The paper discusses the development of energy and performance-efficient embedded software, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The focus of the paper is on the application of complex transformations on the critical parts of the source code, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and algebraic transformations (cs.AR). The paper also mentions loop transformations, which are related to optimization and algorithms (cs.LO), and the need for formal verification, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET).
